Capstone Project - The Battle of Neighborhoods
Introduction – Background and business problem  

Berlin is the most populated city in Germany and it is the capital of that Country. Also for this is one of the most multicultural areas in Germany and it is important also for tourism, creative industries and media. 
More information on the city are available on https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Berlin .
The objective of this project is to use Foursquare location data and regional clustering of venue information to determine what might be the ‘best’ neighbourhood in Berlin to open a restaurant. After traditional north German culinary traditions Italian foods, like pizza and pasta, are among the most popular dishes. Furthermore at December 2019 Italian’s resident in Berlin are at fifth place as population. For this reason there are numerous opportunities to open a new Italian restaurant. 
Through this project, we would find the most suitable location for an entrepreneur to open a new Italian restaurant in Berlin, Germany.
